      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs must be characterized with probability distributions derived from literature or measurement; Monte Carlo propagation must cover all identified uncertain parameters.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ has been performed propagating uncertainty in blood viscosity, hematocrit, and hemolysis model exponents across 500 samples. Input distributions are based on literature ranges. However, the relative contribution of each uncertain input to output variance has not been characterized — sensitivity analysis was deferred to a future assessment cycle. Achieved level 2 against required level 5; dominant input drivers remain uncharacterized."
    },
